  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>Board the Rocky Mountaineer train and explore the two neighbouring provinces of Alberta and British Columbia on one of the most iconic routes through the Rocky Mountains. Passing dramatically-changing countryside while travelling through valleys, canyons and mountain passes. Staying in Banff, Jasper, Kamloops and Vancouver, there is plenty of time to discover the spectacular National Parks and cities western Canada is famous for.</span></p>
<div>
<h2 style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-canada/mountain-rails#Tour highlights">Tour highlights</a> | <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-canada/mountain-rails#Itinerary">Itinerary</a> | <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-canada/mountain-rails#Your holiday includes">Your holiday includes</a> | <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-canada/mountain-rails#Hotels">Hotels </a>| <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/destinations/tours-multi-centres/tours-multi-centres-in-canada/mountain-rails#Departure dates">Departure dates</a></h2>
